#
#  rust-argparse distinctive features:
#    - `ArgumentParser::new()` builder + `.set_description()`
#      / `.set_help()` for program metadata
#    - `.refer(&mut variable)` — bind a target VARIABLE that
#      will be mutated by the parser when this flag/positional
#      is seen
#    - `.add_option(&["-x", "--name"], Action, "help")` —
#      register a FLAG (with leading dashes) with the given
#      ACTION
#    - `.add_argument("name", Action, "help")` — register a
#      POSITIONAL argument (no leading dashes)
#    - `.required()` — mark the most-recently-added flag/arg
#      as required (error if absent)
#    - ACTION TYPES (Python-argparse-inspired):
#      * `Store` — single value (most common; types inferred
#        from target variable)
#      * `StoreTrue` — bool flag set to true
#      * `StoreFalse` — bool flag set to false
#      * `StoreConst(value)` — set a specific constant
#      * `StoreOption` — set Option<T> to Some(value)
#      * `List` — REPEATABLE single-value flag (each occurrence
#        REPLACES); positional VARIADIC
#      * `Collect` — REPEATABLE accumulator (each occurrence
#        APPENDS to a Vec<T>)
#      * `IncrBy(n)` — increment by n per occurrence (counter)
#      * `DecrBy(n)` — decrement by n
#      * `Print(string)` — print constant + exit (useful for
#        custom --license / --about handlers)
#    - SCOPE-BASED BORROW LIFECYCLE — `ap` mutably borrows the
#      target variables for the lifetime of the parse; caller
#      must release the borrow BEFORE using the parsed values
#      (idiomatic pattern: wrap the parse in a `{ ... }` scope)
#    - TYPED CONVERSION via Rust's `FromStr` trait — `Store`
#      with a `u32` target variable parses the value via
#      `<u32 as FromStr>::from_str()`
#    - `parse_args_or_exit()` — convenience entry: parses
#      process::args, prints --help on -h/--help, exits with
#      error message on parse failure
#    - `parse_args(args)` — explicit parsing for custom error
#      handling (returns Result<(), i32> where Err contains
#      exit code)
#    - AUTO --help / -h generation from option/argument
#      descriptions + program description
#    - ABBREVIATION MATCHING — `--ver` matches `--version` if
#      unambiguous (like Python argparse)
#    - NO subcommand framework — flat schema only (caller
#      dispatches manually)
#    - INSPIRED BY Python's argparse module — Paul Colomiets
